#+end_quote

#+begin_quote
[!quote]+ Highlight ([[zotero://open-pdf/library/items/WP66FEUA?page=254&annotation=UVX7BYVJ][Page 254]]) Animal standpoint theory, as I use it, looks at the fundamental role animals play in sustaining the natural world and shaping the human world in co-evolutionary relations. While animals have constituted human existence in beneficial ways, they have seldom been willing partners. The main thesis of animal standpoint theory is that animals have been key determining forces of human psychology, social life, and history overall, and that the domination of human over nonhuman animals underpins the domination of humans over one another and over the natural world.
#+end_quote

#+begin_quote
[!quote]+ Highlight ([[zotero://open-pdf/library/items/WP66FEUA?page=254&annotation=YGDQXFAA][Page 254]]) this approach stresses the systemic consequences of human exploitation of nonhuman animals, the interrelatedness of our fates, and the profound need for revolutionary changes in the way human beings both define themselves and relate to other species and to the earth as a whole. (Pp. 1-2)
