#+begin_quote
[!quote]+ Highlight ([[zotero://open-pdf/library/items/WP66FEUA?page=256&annotation=JUQC9RUU][Page 256]]) Through the animal standpoint we acquire profound ethical insight made possible by a gestalt shift in evaluation, such that a crucial touchstone for gauging the moral character of a society, a culture, or an individual is how people view and treat other animals. One cannot adequately assess the moral worth, philosophical depth, and humanity of either cultures or individuals until one examines their views and relations toward animals and the natural world. (P. 13)
